The tags keyword in Ansible is used to label individual tasks (or groups of tasks) so that you can selectively run only specific parts of a playbook or role — without executing everything every time.

- include_tasks: install.yml
  tags: install

All tasks inside install.yml are tagged install

ansible-playbook playbook.yml - Everything (all tags)
ansible-playbook playbook.yml --tags install - Only tasks from install.yml
Run several tags: --tags install,config
Run all except one: --skip-tags validate
Run tags matching pattern: --tags "install*" (wildcard)

include_vars is a module used to load the variable from file to plays variables

Similar to tasks, roles automatically load only vars/main.yml and defaults/main.yml.

Any other variable file (custom name) must be loaded explicitly — usually with include_vars (or vars_files).
two ways
in tasks/main.yml
